That’s what makes the Gargantua so incredibly dangerous. You walk up to it thinking “oh, what a nicely carved pumpkin”… and WHAM, you’re history! Especially around Halloween they’re absolutely lethal. They could literally be anywhere and go unnoticed. You’d better stay inside come the 31st of the October.
